			<div class="content" id="post-content-3887875">
									

<p>As far as I understand it:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoilers,&nbsp;maybe?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;thoughts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>We're not meant to fully understand what is going on, because Veronica is self-obsessed and projecting, and assumes Hae is already 'in' on all the information, so she gives a very confused an unsatisfactory explanation for what went down. The basic gist, however, is that the SCP (NP rock as a genre) is the product of an awful internal squabble in a band where A) there was loads of relationship drama and everyone hated each other, and B) several members of the band were powerful mages/cosmic horrors.</p>
<p>My best guess at untangling it is as follows:</p>
<p>Veronica (and possibly Jack) hated Sara and Izzy for unclear reasons, possibly related to Jack being jealous of Sara and Izzy being in a relationship, and possibly because Sara was in some culpability for the death of 'Ashy' (who was clearly important to Veronica). Veronica and Jack decided to create a memetic genre sound that would fill the math rock genre (which Sara loved) with samey imitations, thereby ruining it for her. This appears to have been successful, since Sara killed herself (Veronica possibly stole her soul afterwards, but that might also be dramatic hyperbole). In the aftermath, the band imploded, and Izzy underwent some sort of transformation into some sort of horrible eldritch entity ('Brinegash') that also seems to prevent her from playing music.</p>
<p>Veronica assumes the Foundation Agent (Hae) is a minion of Brinegash/Izzy, and kills herself to avoid whatever she thinks Brinegash might have planned as revenge, bequeathing Sara's stolen soul to both her girlfriend Brinegash and Jack (who may have been infatuated with her).</p>
<p>Brad Cameron was seemingly some lucky bastard who got kicked out of the band in favour of Sara before the band got famous/dissolved into eldritch infighting, but who was still on good terms with Veronica. What precise relevance Ashy, the Goddess of Cider, the Man in Bandages, and Ana have, I don't know (though I suspect Ana is Sara's sister, given they have the same number of letters in their name). I don't think we're necessarily supposed to get much more than this outline.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

